= consensus > vote ‚Äî distributed agreement
~sovereign.flow


Èñì

        agreement is slow
                that is the safety

        silence is valid
                waiting is work

        consensus > speed
                sovereignty requires
                        no king


flow
  propose(topic, draft)
  -> deliberate(amendments)
  -> sign(hash)
  -> quorum?
     | yes -> ratify(shared_mem)
     | no  -> wait(pending)


shape
  CONCEPT: ACCORD
  CENTROID
    distributed consensus without central authority
  AXES
    autonomy <-> alignment
    fast <-> safe
    individual <-> collective
  SATELLITES
    msg (transport)
    wake (enforcing blocking)
    sovereign (identity provider)
  VOID
    not majority rule (often unanimity)
    not voting booth
    not committee
  TEXTURE
    the weight of shared intent


impl
  libs
    lib_enclave.consensus
    
  cli
    accord.py [status]      | show pending (default)
    accord.py propose ... @file | body from file (preferred)
    accord.py propose ... "txt" | body from string
    accord.py propose ... - | interactive (human only)
    lib_enclave.sovereign_agent.SovereignAgent
    hashlib (content addressing)

  logic
    proposals in runtime/consensus/
    states: draft, pending, ratified, stale
    signature = Ed25519(hash(body))
    
  cli
    accord.py status <agent>        | check pending
    accord.py propose <topic>       | new draft
    accord.py deliberate <topic>    | review & sign

  output
    "üìú Pending proposals:"
    "  ‚è≥ [TOPIC] (X/Y signatures)"
